  <sect><heading>Getting mpd<label id="getting"></heading>

  <p>
	Mpd is supplied as a
	<bf><htmlurl url="http://www.freebsd.org/ports" name="FreeBSD port">
	</bf>, under the name <bf><tt>net/mpd5</tt></bf>.
	Therefore, the simplest way to get mpd onto your machine
	is to install the mpd package or port.
	For information on how to do this, see the
	<bf><htmlurl url="http://www.freebsd.org/ports"
	name="FreeBSD ports web page"></bf>.
</p>

<p>
	Mpd can also be compiled and installed manually.
	This is useful for example if you want to change the 
	set of device types supported by mpd.

